   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>TRUTH LESSONS LEVEL THREE</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE TYPES IN THE OLD TESTAMENT LESSON THREE THE SACRIFICIAL SKINS, THE SACRIFICES,</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>THE BURNT OFFERINGS,</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>AND THE SEED OF THE WOMAN OUTLINE Concerning Christ s redemption: The sacrificial skins the skins of the sacrifices with which Adam and Eve were clothed: The condition of Adam and Eve before the fall.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>After they sinned, having the sinful conduct, the sinful nature, and the consciousness of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The fallen Adam and Eve making skirts to cover their shame because of their consciousness of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>God clothing them with coats made of the skins of sacrifices, typifying: That God caused Christ to be sacrificed for sinners as the substituting Lamb.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>That God made Christ the righteousness of the sinners who believe in Him that they may be justified and live before God.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The sacrifices the firstlings of the flock with their fat offered by Abel: Abel living before God by offering sacrifices according to God s way of redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The firstlings of the flock which he offered, typifying Christ, who is unto God, who lives for God, and who is gentle and tender.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The fat which he offered, being the fatness of the sheep, typifying the tender merits of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The Christ-redeemed sinners needing to live before God by such a Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The burnt offerings offered by Noah: Noah being saved by God from the old age of corruption into the new age of restoration.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Building an altar to offer sacrifices as burnt offerings.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>This being the accomplishment of the initial types of Christ s redemption: The burnt offering typifying the perfect Christ becoming a sweet-smelling savor unto God.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>That the earth might remain before God, signifying that the earth might minister to God.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Concerning Christ s salvation: The seed of the woman the one who would save man: Typifying Christ, who was born of a virgin.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To bruise the head of the serpent for man, typifying that Christ would destroy Satan.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The ancient serpent the one who was to be destroyed: Signifying the subtle one, the devil, Satan.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>To bruise the heel of the seed of the woman, typifying that Satan would hurt Christ, who caused Satan s death.</S>
   </TEXT>
